skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "0e74fd80-c6ee-4404-b614-220af30f100c", "value": "Buildings, engineering constructions and machinery, used for the purpose of supplying a town, or region with water distributed through pipes."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "c1123233-1992-4b09-abd3-36e949c3333f", "value": "Historic Characterization Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "e41843e1-fc66-44ab-82a2-092d13e3d438", "value": "Thesaurus combining Historic Landscape and Historic Seascape Characterization terminology (e.g. reclaimed land, vineyard, dunes)."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "0891ad56-e2e5-47ac-8872-0963249c7333", "value": "An area of foreshore where the predominant cover is exposed fine rock sediments of a grain size generally perceived as 'sand'."}
{"id": "08ff2fa3-3842-46f7-be7e-0e19ec2f85f4", "value": "Large-scale commercial base for air travel."}
{"id": "950b91ab-02bb-4e14-b0e3-b0064123f941", "value": "Buildings and associated structures and areas for safely guiding air traffic into and out of an airport."}

{"id": "b317bf16-7b99-45b3-b4f3-4002fc8e30a3", "value": "Areas characterised by commercial fishing using hand nets worked by an individual fisherman. This consists of a rectangular frame from which a net is suspended. Regional variations include haaf netting, lave netting and dip netting."}
{"id": "7d57b945-d460-430f-bebc-069878dda8d3", "value": "A piece of land used for the cultivation of hops."}
{"id": "7b9b6517-99ac-469c-947b-a0d07b549a1a", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the retrieval, refining, processing and storage of petroleum oil."}

{"id": "f0b315ff-2f6f-474d-9110-d25f63f18a10", "value": "Cable laid on or beneath the sea floor and used to transmit electricity from the mainland to islands or to offshore installations, or to link offshore electricity generators to the onshore national electricity grid."}
{"id": "ae4429c6-4833-46dc-a9e2-85941c16ae0f", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the generation of electricity."}
{"id": "5448c302-6183-44b2-9a02-7679aa9bcf8e", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the distribution of electricity."}

{"id": "7d90f358-75a3-402b-8560-922c0a5d1120", "value": "Industrial area for the decommissioning of structures associated with the nuclear industry, reprocessing of nuclear materials, nuclear waste management and/or nuclear fuel manufacturing activities take place."}

{"id": "72994674-f658-41cd-9c5a-19615169de1b", "value": "A conduit or pipes, used primarily for conveying liquid or gas such as petroleum from oil wells to a refinery, or for supplying water to a town or district, etc."}
{"id": "a55faab0-912b-40b9-8806-ca9a91607800", "value": "Raised cable supported on pylons or other structures and used to transmit electricity over long distances."}
{"id": "203fadd3-98a6-4476-b133-1f39388c191c", "value": "Water meadow with relatively rigid patterns of drains, usually perfectly straight and with large numbers parallel with each other."}
{"id": "cc42618a-8456-4900-85c1-45f9824d8bc9", "value": "Water meadow with a relatively irregular pattern of drains, usually more sinuous and with fewer being parallel with each other."}

{"id": "00f5602b-3d04-415d-b4c3-796f93d79320", "value": "Controlled irrigation to draw nutrient-rich silts and material onto valley-bottom grassland to increase hay yields and enable earlier mowing. Early modern agricultural improvement; normally now no longer operated though earthworks may survive."}
{"id": "890f5f8a-c10d-4121-b38b-8a6ee35a430d", "value": "Rough grassland left open, not divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "aa936899-bc90-44ec-a5fd-3bd186cc23b9", "value": "A site for the disposal of waste materials by burial."}

{"id": "14f21327-9a1f-488c-9e23-e54ee1eb8512", "value": "Patterns of early fields, often prehistoric in origin, that are roughly rectilinear with sinuous sides and that share a common general orientation without having the dominant lines of coaxial fields. Sometimes called Celtic Fields."}

{"id": "36a3a008-67f1-471b-8564-fdf5679f75e3", "value": "Field system with prevailing orientation.Most boundaries are straight or nearly so and closely align with main axis or run perpendicular to it. Usually prehistoric or early medieval. Suggestive of early planned land allotment."}
{"id": "453bed23-67f8-4f73-9ade-06b4deb6f862", "value": "Medieval fields, often large and regular, established on the food producing estates of monasteries."}

{"id": "2389aa7e-c2fe-45b8-86f9-6ba21083ad19", "value": "A coaxial field system with two perpendicular lines of axis, forming a grid-like field pattern. Often possible to establish a more dominant axis."}

{"id": "f4fe0ada-b969-464e-a13c-de6114be3875", "value": "Field patterns established by lord of an estate, usually as closes (bounded individual fields), in distinction to the open common fields of tenants. They tend to be relatively large fields."}

{"id": "e66aa6da-8cac-4ebb-a549-7538f2e49c46", "value": "Early farmland, whose predominant character developed by the later medieval or earlier. Usually broad-brush characterisation that includes farming settlement and various other land use."}

{"id": "83841aea-ddfd-4181-b4c3-0a908c96f686", "value": "Land enclosed from woodland. Required licence in medieval period. Term applied more generally in landscape history. Can include planned and regular enclosures and piecemeal irregular ones. Often still with numerous trees on boundaries."}

{"id": "89179f33-8047-491b-b2ca-f95c8b5f10a8", "value": "Meaning varies: In Scotland a holding of enclosed farmland, in Cornwall later medieval and post-medieval enclosure containing rough ground used for grazing and furze. In central England a strip of garden attached to a messuage in a medieval village."}

{"id": "9985ca01-77fe-4a79-938a-76a6d90713bc", "value": "Field systems derived from gradual enclosure of open fields, usually from 13C to 17 & 18C when Parliamentary Enclosure dominated. Individual strips or groups enclosed by landholders, leaving elements of the former open field pattern visible."}

{"id": "1588598a-211f-471a-895d-08170ad69224", "value": "System of fields in which several farmers held land in common, intermixed in narrow strips assessable via length and width, with low or no separating boundaries. Mostly medieval. Few survive. Lost to piecemeal or planned enclosure, 13th - 20th century."}

{"id": "41f1217f-0a42-46b6-a2f5-73392775ce11", "value": "Fields that can be demonstrated by to be either prehistoric or early medieval in origin by virtue of either form or direct association with early farming settlement."}

{"id": "d57ff72b-bde1-4b0b-bfa1-0b7477772104", "value": "Areas whose surface predominantly comprises bedrock exposures. On the sea-floor can be associated with rocks and boulders but little finer sediment deposition."}
{"id": "eff9707e-4a36-47f5-8ee1-ec525c9d220d", "value": "Large areas of seafloor whose surface sediments predominantly comprise different grades of sand and very low silt and clay content."}

{"id": "a24faae2-0243-48a2-9bf9-8d70dee3c80c", "value": "An area of sand banks containing extensive wavelike structures and megaripples formed by rapidly moving currents of water on the sandbanks' surface. May occur around the margins of sandflats or they may occur in deeper water."}

{"id": "96014a61-afbc-46ea-baa6-f161f59e26e5", "value": "Extensive areas of seafloor whose surface sediments predominantly comprise different grades of pebbles, rocks, boulders etc with lower sand and very low silt and clay contents."}
{"id": "b7c99d41-1111-48c2-b27c-9687eb6c0941", "value": "Extensive areas of seafloor whose surface sediments predominantly comprise fine sediment grades with high silt and clay contents."}

{"id": "5c8e716a-947c-4523-bc35-8a1d4018cb27", "value": "Large areas of seafloor whose surface sediments predominantly comprise heterogeneous sediment grades, from pebbles and gravels to sands, silts and clays. The overall composition can be highly variable, as can the form of their grades' mixing."}
{"id": "738ebb84-7ee9-4e74-859d-e14cb48573b4", "value": "Of the sea, at any or all of its layers: surface, water column, floor and sub-floor."}
{"id": "d1faee14-754a-43c4-b495-bf1468e54754", "value": "Long sheds, into which railway lines run, used to house railway engines."}
{"id": "dcea7a07-592c-4ff4-a91d-737f2e9b1697", "value": "Buildings and structures associated with railway transport."}

{"id": "42bcbf6e-7239-411e-9901-315ebe50bd8f", "value": "System of rail tracks along which passenger carriages or goods wagons are moved, usually by locomotive engines. Usually includes beds, cuttings, embankments, tunnels etc."}
{"id": "05782443-1431-411d-8b06-f83469b9ad10", "value": "Where railway trains stop to load and unload passengers or freight. Includes buildings and directly related grounds."}

{"id": "b6ec2ab8-7417-421a-825f-84bc7b0f68e1", "value": "A light railway. Early usage tended to be in industrial contexts with animal drawn stock; later usage tended to be for the conveyance of passengers, often in urban areas, with vehicles run along sunken rails."}
{"id": "2ac0c6e3-355b-47c9-a491-6966111c3485", "value": "Complex, often attached to a railway station where engines, coaches and wagons are laid up and maintained."}

{"id": "8e92bb0f-0239-49f1-b668-eb531f2da654", "value": "A short piece of track lying parallel to the main railway line enabling trains and trucks to either pass one another or be parked when not in use."}
{"id": "880e47c7-1739-4210-85f7-ff412fa0d9ed", "value": "A bridge carrying a railway track."}
{"id": "0479d4a6-0be1-4323-987d-96ca32d34810", "value": "A tunnel through which a railway line runs."}
{"id": "97991285-224a-4334-a113-26baea2195c9", "value": "Valley side rough ground divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "a7809631-2fa2-411e-a990-d6eb0f896cba", "value": "Heathland divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "3b0e925d-cef8-4cbe-9f1a-3aefe644ece8", "value": "A place from which gold is extracted. Includes closely associated spoil, processing, and transport facilities."}
{"id": "05c10240-e5d8-4b24-afa6-4af85a02eea9", "value": "Sea or river channels, charted or otherwise, recorded as in active use by present shipping traffic, whatever the channels' date of origin."}

{"id": "94f608e7-9e85-40f7-a2e6-ba0afab27462", "value": "Sea and river channels no longer charted or recorded as in active navigational use for present shipping traffic, whatever the channel's broad date of origin."}
{"id": "8df39a2f-509d-4619-bac8-6afda78fa840", "value": "Sea and river channels, charted or otherwise, used for shipping traffic. Use more specific type were known."}
{"id": "35995081-e8cb-4ba7-ad1a-531f5a766a21", "value": "Take-off and landing lane with permanent surface."}
{"id": "453c041b-08c6-4f09-bfad-69b3963df790", "value": "Large sheds for the housing and maintainence of aircraft, etc."}

{"id": "1446b5d5-d401-4526-8960-e5120f05833c", "value": "A landing and taking-off area for military aircraft. Often includes ancilliary structures and buildings for the maintenance and storage of aircraft, defence of the site, accommodation of staff, controlling airspace etc."}

{"id": "05947029-19d6-4c8f-8bb3-d7a7be67f5d2", "value": "Cables laid beneath the sea to carry telecommunications including telephone and internet communications, also historic telegraph systems. The most frequent function of submarine cabling, especially that covering long distances."}

{"id": "4365323c-ed5e-49a7-aa2c-925192c20476", "value": "Areas variously submerged but also subject to exposure above the sea surface at various states of the tide, known as 'drying areas' and forming a hazard to the safe passage of shipping."}
{"id": "2cf630eb-c5cc-43ff-b570-962bd277d843", "value": "Scrub divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "79336734-53e0-4e0d-9885-bbf0fa0d5802", "value": "Scrub left open, not divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "73c011b4-3e78-479c-bc70-950d20f2b15a", "value": "Uncultivated land characterised by vegetation dominated by shrubs or bushes of woody plants, sometimes including small trees."}
{"id": "4522b1a8-4195-4bd2-9889-5fe07ca5a4b5", "value": "Ancient woodland that consists of broadleaved and coniferous trees, often the product of modern replanting."}
{"id": "e49c0c98-7f6b-4a36-a2eb-7fbb7ec643b8", "value": "A grand residence, royal, aristocratic or ecclesiastical, rural or urban, with immediately associated yards and offices."}

{"id": "0d66f912-595c-4122-94ab-74d7e4aa0aa3", "value": "Gentry house in a rural setting, normally within a landscape park, and usually accompanied by a range of attached and detached offices, yards, etc."}
{"id": "33e58c96-a93b-48e1-9866-8c198e3768e5", "value": "A tunnel through which a road runs."}
{"id": "2efd5a17-8bd3-4d83-8a83-c72da376be48", "value": "Coastal base for the docking, launch and maintenance of submarines."}

{"id": "76c08f15-9caf-4e31-a87e-6cc681dd6b99", "value": "Part of a landscape garden or park planted to give an uncultivated appearance, often using exotic or unusual trees and shrubs. Usually provided with networks of pathways, often more formally arranged than the term might suggest."}
{"id": "c1bc5a3b-f25b-4791-9e91-3d088c327d20", "value": "A complex of buildings and areas in which a range of weaponry and techniques are developed and trialled."}

{"id": "a0c89724-b6b7-4c7b-a812-884d41fc7e75", "value": "An artificial structure or group of structures enclosing an area of water which was impounded by lock gates to maintain water levels artificially, facilitating the loading, unloading, building or repair of ships."}
{"id": "40d2caf7-dfee-493c-a105-350298d2982b", "value": "A site including a pitch, stands and other ancillary buildings and areas associated with playing and paying to watch the game of football."}
{"id": "521dd101-65b6-4ee1-8313-fe96fe6bfd6e", "value": "Area largely devoted to retail; typically at a hub within a town or city."}

{"id": "b369276b-1f23-4700-8c00-cf76dca3ab16", "value": "Large urban settlement, including residential, industrial, civic, commercial and business areas. Usually having a cathedral within its bounds. Often a central place within a region, with subsidiary towns etc."}

{"id": "a3f96a9b-cb2d-474b-9199-81964b9d3031", "value": "Settlement normally larger than a village, smaller than a city, usually with some administrative autonomy. Early towns often walled. Mixes of public and private buildings and spaces, and residential, civic, commercial and industrial areas."}
{"id": "d322278f-f6d8-4b38-9871-7ccd03126f0c", "value": "A factory used for the manufacture of textiles."}
{"id": "6d8f179e-597a-45bb-be9e-af71320de28f", "value": "A factory used for processing raw materials. Use more specific mill type where known."}
{"id": "83353d35-9431-41b2-b956-8f4024538f85", "value": "A tunnel through which a canal runs."}

{"id": "9a03370d-c7ac-4f3d-aa3b-83d684db1ec9", "value": "Artificial watercourse, usually connecting existing watercourses or bodies, constructed for the purpose of inland navigation and transportation or irrigation. Nowadays also used for recreational purposes."}
{"id": "b94336e4-e6e8-4d41-a31c-a73541b38ceb", "value": "The removal of oil, oil derivatives or natural gas from naturally occurring reserves."}

{"id": "547f4db2-e795-4333-93d8-2058016fe62d", "value": "A pipeline involved in the transmission of oil or natural gas between facilities involved in their extraction, processing, storage or distribution."}
{"id": "d14bf001-f770-4b40-a7ce-fa034e09ca7c", "value": "A mine used for the extraction of tin bearing ore."}
{"id": "6b8d7a20-8878-4943-a90e-32b37b34be83", "value": "A building or part of a building and directly associated grounds, used for the storage of goods or merchandise."}

{"id": "86b86435-57ea-47a7-b68e-0dca65a56a8d", "value": "Buildings & grounds used specifically for storage of fish or fish products. Such storage may relate to several aspects of the fishing industry, for example the storage of fish after landing & before auction or sale, or the cold storage of fish after sale."}
{"id": "6d2ea9c0-8eb5-47b7-ac7f-d59e31243899", "value": "A place where several roads meet, often negotiated using roundabouts."}
{"id": "a8940d56-410a-43e9-9579-f4f4197415ac", "value": "Rough Grassland divided by stock-proof boundaries."}

{"id": "35f332b0-453d-4b6b-be5b-332e84c6531a", "value": "Area of rough ground dominated by unintensively managed grassland often the result of long traditions of rough grazing or a conservation measure to prevent land reverting to scrub."}
{"id": "bc2863cb-4ebc-4d71-a133-2c408ca44495", "value": "A pond or pool with arms covered with nets into which wild birds, are allured and then caught or shot."}
{"id": "b91c7d8a-c5b0-4ee4-b435-5e6f0a777447", "value": "A factory or plant for the manufacture of ice using mechanised refrigeration techniques."}
{"id": "805d9bc7-4bfc-4923-92c1-2817aac11bf0", "value": "Places of permanent or temporary residence."}
{"id": "4b0fa5c3-2fb6-4f4b-b7cd-06d2df0aa139", "value": "Residential area dominated by houses joined to just one other to form one building."}
{"id": "39eb674d-a02b-4b16-997a-b9d05b2bf3dc", "value": "Residential area dominated by purpose-built tenement buildings, each containing several flats or apartments."}

{"id": "f90fcc11-8895-4f81-aba9-0ca7db336800", "value": "Residential area dominated by lines of attached houses, usually planned and built as one unit. Often associated with industrial towns. Sometimes follow earlier patterns, such as those of the fields they overlay."}
{"id": "51f95291-cc91-422e-8bbe-da4e48561e16", "value": "Residential area dominated by free-standing houses that are not joined to others on any side."}
{"id": "ee950579-cdae-4e2e-85ca-1ba1e678b157", "value": "A site where natural gas produced by geological processes is extracted from deep beneath the earth's surface."}
{"id": "8e8a818e-46fe-46ec-b985-d6038c699210", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the retrieval, refining, processing and storage of natural gas."}
{"id": "275e1b3d-0bdd-403f-9334-8e47e821b72e", "value": "An enclosed area where wild animals are bred, studied and exhibited to the public."}
{"id": "19ebee94-8aa7-4d88-87f0-03d1a80070f1", "value": "A public recreational complex centred around an open-air swimming pool."}

{"id": "cdd94f92-c322-4dba-9153-ac0235d9b15d", "value": "Land, often in urban areas, dedicated to outdoor public recreation. Usually with ornamental planting of trees and shrubs, with some formal gardens, ornamental ponds etc. Generally more robust than in landscaped parks with public conveniences & playgrounds"}
{"id": "5c749c0f-cc3f-4f66-9c52-b18c298704e3", "value": "Area of open ground with permanent or semi-permanent facilities established to enable people to enjoy, amuse or please themselves."}

{"id": "4cccfc9d-d3fe-4b13-b236-76d273199d3b", "value": "A building, group of buildings or space within a building, where objects of value such as works of art, antiquities, scientific specimens, or other artefacts are housed and displayed."}

{"id": "c0bacf96-2712-4b32-b2a1-9ba4eeb96cc1", "value": "Low-lying land often covered by water and usually with peaty vegetation. Used seasonally for grazing. Historically, peat was sometimes cut as domestic fuel and the area also used for trapping wildfowl."}

{"id": "19abea4b-30c4-4f13-a736-45f7ec792364", "value": "Areas of relatively mobile, thick deposits of clays, silts, organic detritus and some very fine sand content, submerged at high tide and exposed at low tide, and often expressed as areas of muddy banks in sheltered areas along estuary sides."}

{"id": "19fc6536-76e1-4a6b-8130-f291b89ee051", "value": "Areas of relatively mobile, thick sand deposits, submerged at high tide and exposed at low tide, and often expressed as areas of sandbanks detached from the shore by tidal channels."}

{"id": "7c013998-ed80-4570-aff5-7702126400c3", "value": "Coastally situated or inter-tidal areas of permanently saturated land such as saltmarsh whose vegetation and extents of open water may be dominated by its slope and elevation relative to the tidal cycle."}
{"id": "e22b648d-b670-44b1-bec6-b166a1da1dad", "value": "Chalk grassland, divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "f814123d-dc25-4531-a4f2-cb4b366ed247", "value": "Field or plot, often with hangars and other buildings, used for commercial or private helicopter travel."}
{"id": "a3e8a558-94e5-4fe8-b615-3e2a5a1a1818", "value": "Features associated with control, accommodation, servicing and testing of aircraft."}
{"id": "7e08f64e-5386-47be-ae6a-191a3d198987", "value": "Small-scale commercial or private field used for air travel, mainly fixed-wing."}
{"id": "219e8d76-3c43-4158-a0c0-cbf49acaf55a", "value": "Buildings and their directly associated grounds at an airport from where passengers await, embark and disembark from an aircraft."}
{"id": "3cd87bb5-738a-4f02-811b-f07caae84a6c", "value": "A building or place where aircraft can be stored and maintained."}
{"id": "4ae22305-e931-4f26-bfa4-26218ace55c4", "value": "Marshland divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "3636e834-a188-43fb-ae39-b754505f13ef", "value": "Land within a generally built-up area, previously either open or used differently, that has been used for further construction."}

{"id": "fbb56ee7-4441-4333-ba16-c220111ecaa2", "value": "A planned town that developed from the Garden City Movement of the early 20th century, founded by Ebenezer Howard, and promoting the idea of separating residential and industrial/commercial areas with bands of parkland."}
{"id": "5a20d2e9-89d8-444e-bb44-5a05fde6bdf5", "value": "An accumulation of broken rock debris found on the slopes and at the base of crags, mountain cliffs, or valley shoulders."}

{"id": "06d75920-e626-4779-8428-cf609d436366", "value": "A tall, steep and largely exposed face of the local geological formation, usually of rock though in some areas cliffs may form from erosion of softer materials such as boulder clay."}
{"id": "1b1b8a80-5aeb-44ea-812e-7cb6de87a51e", "value": "A large, steep elevation in the earth's surface with a relatively small surface area on its summit."}
{"id": "8ea092e4-e0dc-4ffd-b6cd-d5c6db78cf42", "value": "Area used for recreational sailing, yachting and other small craft persuits."}
{"id": "ec886ab1-f1dd-4366-aa76-2e2fd2209988", "value": "Buildings and structures used for sending and receiving signals."}
{"id": "e3f26b15-9d50-4201-b318-9fc3670ed08b", "value": "A site and associated buildings used by the military for various purposes, usually defensive."}

{"id": "0b8c8615-2cef-407d-8bb3-1261153f855a", "value": "Areas, sites and linked systems of such involved in the passive or active defence of the country against hostile forces on land, sea and in the air."}
{"id": "6871c88d-1506-4c41-8bda-52a04c139180", "value": "A defensive work, usually permanent. Use specific type where known."}
{"id": "461de589-37de-450d-bd6c-c4b70c3d91a4", "value": "A residence for military personnel."}

{"id": "b10875db-5ab5-4bcc-9206-038aaf9a0f82", "value": "Complexes for transport, storage and deployment of military vehicles, vessels, aircraft etc and their associated armaments. Can also, as in the case of airfields, cover complexes actively employed in defence and aggression."}
{"id": "50bd1e99-8a61-40b9-add9-f8767a31be49", "value": "Areas used by armed forces on land or at sea for training and military exercises."}

{"id": "d47bf7de-4cef-4aaf-ad5f-4b661053f453", "value": "Recorded areas of former battles, where they form the dominant character of, or are the chief historical association attached to those areas."}

{"id": "4ec844ea-1457-443b-b4b7-d647e3f8f10b", "value": "A stone-faced enclosure, with entrance closed by a floatable caisson or by gates, which can be pumped dry for inspection, maintenance, or repair of the hull or underwater fittings of a ship or ships."}

{"id": "dd9b9b12-ba9e-4569-96ae-91e7131db57d", "value": "A site where copper is mined. Includes closely associated spoil, processing and transport facilities. Also use MINE plus other relevant ore name as appropriate."}
{"id": "88cc467b-61f2-4315-9ca7-b3974460d007", "value": "Areas of woodland consisting of both broadleaved and coniferous trees."}

{"id": "b1c210cb-144f-466c-94a5-d4e3c1951a35", "value": "Set of local authority provided dwellings for rent. Usually of uniform design, with gardens, and often located either at the edges of villages or at the roadside in open country."}
{"id": "26ff6c69-b204-4cfb-b78d-b5a7461e38ab", "value": "A supporting structure for drilling machinery used in the extraction of, or prospecting for, mineral oils."}
{"id": "21f2cfdb-5ba5-43a2-b34a-95e789dcd538", "value": "A lake, sometimes purpose built, for use in the sport of rowing."}
{"id": "18a1f402-e831-45fb-857d-dad2a58abe1b", "value": "Public outdoor areas often with facilities for games and other activities."}

{"id": "8e29310b-6e81-438b-96b2-ea27ece15928", "value": "An area of parkland where animals are exhibited to the public but, unlike a zoo where they would occupy cages or small enclosures, are allowed to roam a large open environment."}

{"id": "79b87853-384d-4be6-b13b-f36237762f13", "value": "An area of managed countryside designated for visitors to enjoy recreations, such as walking specified parks and trails, in a rural environment. Often provides public facilities such as car parking, toilets, cafes and visitor information."}

{"id": "444119de-dc27-4fe5-aa69-178500755960", "value": "An area set aside for growing watercress. As the watercress requires large quantities of slightly alkaline water the beds are usually sited around the headwaters of chalk streams."}

{"id": "7f1b2a48-ff56-437b-bfb0-b96983e8ee45", "value": "Permanent grassland on poorly drained valley floors, exploited for the lush grass it supports. Often enclosed, sometimes held in common and used for hay-making and best summer pasture."}
{"id": "b6139c32-739b-4deb-bfa3-a4afd807f599", "value": "Water management system typically with weir, leat, mill pool, mill and its associated structures, spaces and tailrace."}
{"id": "0792f334-29e9-46cd-8cad-d5dc46891aa9", "value": "Areas, often enclosed by stock-proof boundaries, where willows are cultivated for various purposes, including basketry, but also for fuel."}
{"id": "5ae8c4ac-7e7e-41fb-abf9-7c44c336bef5", "value": "An unlit, highly visible and distinctive feature on the coast that can be used by mariners for navigation during daylight only."}
{"id": "1d1633f1-71a2-4ccc-93cf-553307a0cd07", "value": "A prominent structure situated on land specifically as a guide to navigation or warning to sailors."}

{"id": "07ee1af7-3cc8-4fad-a26b-b82dbed7d213", "value": "A body of shallow salt, brackish or fresh water totally or partially enclosed from the sea by a sand bar, spit or reef running across the entrance."}

{"id": "987d1e73-3990-4742-aa75-4cc24009c076", "value": "An area within an ornamentally designed landscape where owners and guests walked about for pleasure. Typically complex mixes of plantings, ornamental gardens and play areas (bowling, croquet, etc)."}

{"id": "c1bda1c0-5341-4f6c-ae39-268877f5c71d", "value": "A garden that has been designed for the purpose of aesthetic pleasure, rather than the production of crops and usually an element of ornamentally designed landscapes."}

{"id": "d6c7b259-2506-4e17-b056-2d6ef0591650", "value": "A botanical garden, as an element of a designed or ornamental landscape, designed specifically for the cultivation and display of, often rare, trees."}
{"id": "5615787d-b709-4ce7-814d-31ec93f29e4b", "value": "An area in which local sewage is filtered and purified in large rectangular or circular tanks."}
{"id": "9b3525b4-d533-425e-b51a-4ec574476775", "value": "A complex including buildings providing accomadation and activity areas for those involved in equestrian sports/activities and their horses."}
{"id": "5974fb47-3931-4b95-b1f4-e9e71894581e", "value": "An area of prepared ground on which a sport is played and where paying spectators watch. Use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "c46ee71c-d69f-4671-91de-ce0a2b85f253", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with water sporting activities. Use more specific type where known."}

{"id": "ef6b68f2-59f8-45e6-b087-416220d5ec5a", "value": "An area of ground, often publically owned, where outdoor sports are played, usually with the necessary marking out and structures (goal posts etc). Distinguished from sports grounds where spectators pay to watch."}

{"id": "15ee6166-3b0d-4863-9e53-549525176b24", "value": "Areas whose dominant character is provision for sporting activity, whether or not commercially provided, and whether or not in areas of purpose-built structures."}
{"id": "7716194f-5558-4a41-9e4e-c3bc7234dc58", "value": "Areas relating to the sport that involves breeding and training thoroughbred horses and racing them against each other on large courses."}
{"id": "ddfcd6a1-cde3-4148-ac32-f1ca84572f17", "value": "A site including artillery pieces and associated structures directed out to sea to engage enemy shipping and defend the coastline."}
{"id": "a7f0da9f-4e0a-4e6c-b2d7-8df89ad05001", "value": "An area of defensive installations on the coast designed for use against emeny attacks or invasion on the coast by sea or air."}
{"id": "dca5dc84-6223-4196-b306-2a34ace591fa", "value": "A dock or basin on the coast, an estuary or an inland waterway, used for mooring yachts and other small pleasure craft."}
{"id": "4174e4eb-16e9-4502-9bed-8637bb17d3ad", "value": "A place from which granite is excavated."}
{"id": "72e9d734-974b-4c0c-be52-418e2f6a5bd5", "value": "A site where marble is extracted from the ground."}

{"id": "65072c3d-bb7e-491c-8ac8-d37d57de6729", "value": "A place from which shale, a laminated clay or silt which has been compressed by the weight of the rocks over it, is extracted from the ground."}
{"id": "92431646-b4a2-4c0d-868a-0abef7388e5e", "value": "A site where cementstone nodules are extracted."}
{"id": "9fccb869-dc61-4567-92e4-2ce4e578e9fd", "value": "A place from which sandstone is excavated."}
{"id": "ba8dcd74-9dbe-4bf6-b789-5145016545c9", "value": "A place from which slate is quarried from the ground."}
{"id": "6a52e666-266a-4acd-bd8a-d5188d1d0639", "value": "An excavation from which stone for building, hardcore, hedging etc is obtained by cutting, blasting, hoisting, crushing, dressing etc."}
{"id": "00935fd9-7d65-44a1-ad8a-2180ecf69c89", "value": "A place from which limestone is extracted. Includes closely associated spoil, processing, and transport facilities."}
{"id": "5996a17f-233e-4415-a716-7eb7766f19f5", "value": "A place from which gypsum is excavated."}
{"id": "382bdfdc-2c1b-4c99-b196-1aa2a845a418", "value": "Length of river sufficiently deep for regular use by water transport and traffic."}
{"id": "b9e98264-d4b8-49b3-ab64-d493eab56920", "value": "Natural and artificial passages for inland waterborne travel and transport."}

{"id": "1a8464f6-e3e9-4d12-aa2a-593e58e9e84c", "value": "Village whose regularity of spacing and shape of plots, and also often of form of dwellings, suggests a degree of external planning, usually by a landlord."}
{"id": "a9fc7250-ced1-4a84-9c17-4e4a69146966", "value": "Ancient woodland that predominantly consists of coniferous trees, often the products of modern replanting."}
{"id": "d9890e6b-f0a9-4bae-be72-10e5d031d9e3", "value": "Areas of woodland dominated by broadleaved trees."}

{"id": "8539ea85-dd82-48b7-8c17-9a34a08449c2", "value": "Woodland planted deliberately, either for landscaping or to produce a crop of timber. Mid 20th century plantations usually single spicies conifers often plated in rows. Earlier plantations and those of the late 20th century onwards are often more mixed."}
{"id": "0ced24b5-e82a-4463-b49a-5fc95963740d", "value": "In HLC used for woodland that has not been classified as ancient, plantation or secondary."}
{"id": "da387d50-b449-491f-bb0b-b7540b9b02c8", "value": "Areas of woodland dominated by coniferous trees."}

{"id": "6638f6ef-e1b4-4056-b940-8fe7a111c54c", "value": "Area of managed woodland, usually oak, ash, hornbeam, hazel, alder, willow or beech, periodically cut to encourage new growth providing a source of smaller timber; for rods, fuel, charcoal etc. Larger coppies often divided into cropping areas or coups."}
{"id": "ef3af9f5-69ce-4434-a4ae-11bd8e3b5d03", "value": "A woodland that has had its original tree coverage felled and replaced with new trees, often coniferous."}

{"id": "891e6338-c5da-4127-94d0-5b5e787d5a63", "value": "Woodland that has developed, usually by natural colonization, on land formerly used for other purposes (agriculture, settlement, industry etc). If this process pre-dated 1600, secondary woodland can be classified as ancient woodland."}

{"id": "e4e86d20-bb1e-423a-9905-3612a7f0b8ba", "value": "Woodland believed to have existed since at least 1600 in England and in England defined as such by Natural England. Usually managed for timber, coppice etc and often contains dividing banks, trackways, charcoal burning platforms etc."}

{"id": "fb1b6190-0a95-4bb0-962b-8ea7397b9852", "value": "Scattered trees within grassland, the trees providing shelter for forage as well as being harvested for timber and fuel. Now most often found within deer parks, but more widespread, especially on steep slopes, in the medieval period."}

{"id": "5d2f2f1e-7036-4a7a-ba17-4b746505ed29", "value": "Areas characterised by the use of semi permanent/permanent fish traps for the capture of naturally occurring fish stocks. Does not include temporary portable pots and creels which are covered by POTTING AREA."}
{"id": "eb94a195-d29f-4062-8049-68f40337cd0f", "value": "A private garden established primarily for growing vegetables and soft and bush fruit for domestic consumption."}
{"id": "ffe5abf1-fcc5-4c21-8eed-a83ef5964779", "value": "A farmhouse and ancillary farm buildings forming the operational centre for the surrounding farmland."}
{"id": "ef262618-a305-4efb-be04-ccd7239a5b3d", "value": "Coastal rough ground left open, undivided by stock-proof boundaries."}

{"id": "e43dbfc7-f801-44e2-8250-45d1c329f8c8", "value": "Coastal area with rough vegetation created and maintained by grazing, often seasonal, and by fuel collection. Much is now neglected and reverting to scrub."}
{"id": "754105f9-8df6-4ad4-91fa-880c963d7fbd", "value": "Coastal rough ground divided by stock-proof boundaries."}

{"id": "6c65c6d2-8f61-418e-b2dc-2a6f0c88244e", "value": "A building within a transport terminal, often associated with the registration and clearing of incoming and outgoing passengers or freight. Also used for waiting and so often provided with commercial outlets and other facilities."}

{"id": "ee86f6c9-1cfd-43bd-a2ff-c6e8137313b2", "value": "A small, irregular enclosure taken from formerly open land, usually common land. Sometimes associated with industrial activity and/or routes of access. Normally later medieval or early post-medieval."}

{"id": "81b5432a-3920-4e45-9250-91faf7e2cef4", "value": "A market where fish is sold. Includes closely and functionally associated open areas, built structures, wharves, quays and distribution facilities."}
{"id": "f4a9b331-4b68-4c33-95a9-c74270d4c477", "value": "An area of grass, marked out for use in the game of cricket."}
{"id": "0732a51a-9c7f-4f31-af9d-01db35c1fded", "value": "Secondary woodland whose species are largely broadleaved."}

{"id": "a2045d18-83e2-469c-a502-11ad96c42e4a", "value": "An area of a port, dock or harbour where cargo vessels load and unload large storage containers. Includes associated container storage areas and rail terminals for containers transported to the terminal by rail."}

{"id": "cd8dc66a-376e-4266-aa93-52e942a1db47", "value": "A port, dock or harbour where ferries, hovercraft, ocean liners and cargo vessels can load and unload. May include road and/or rail terminals for transportation to the port."}

{"id": "443e7d14-7405-4188-936c-57c9ed7748f4", "value": "An area of a port, dock or harbour, often including buildings for passport control, customs and for sheltered waiting and storage, where passengers and vehicles using ferry services can embark/disembark and where supplies can be taken on board."}
{"id": "698f4cc8-6063-4afa-9614-41c81e68549b", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the processing of timber."}
{"id": "3d8a2e15-8a53-4e34-ac08-6c3e495dfc60", "value": "An open yard or place where timber is stacked or stored."}

{"id": "e504fc7b-0ce6-4fd9-9649-ca509c16049e", "value": "Recorded areas of former naval battles, where they form the dominant character of those areas. They may be associated with enhanced material imprints still extant in the form of wrecks and debris."}

{"id": "b62b0bec-341c-415c-b5e6-9cdee198ec34", "value": "Fortified residence, usually of a noble and usually medieval or early post-medieval in date. Castle forms developed through time although some features, such as curtain walls and gatehouses, were common throughout."}
{"id": "6e86def0-4465-413f-af90-9af2a1fd044a", "value": "A building or site used for the storage and distribution of fuel for military purposes."}
{"id": "d19331df-e0e8-4c91-98cd-e44d601dbdfe", "value": "An area used by the armed forces for the storage and issuing of military stores and materials."}

{"id": "3f2e987d-7a2b-42fc-b001-dea2781d06ef", "value": "An area usually with a building or group of buildings, often enclosed by a system of fortifications, used by an armed force for the storage and distribution of military equipment."}

{"id": "b106d09b-afb6-4132-bb4e-3ea7beb09cee", "value": "Farmland, whose predominant character developed between the medieval period and WW2. Usually broad-brush characterisation that includes farming settlement and various land use."}

{"id": "653b1f18-13ec-47a6-9d20-9c73faccafce", "value": "Land, often public, let out to individuals or an individual for the purposes of cultivation or other land use. Often in numerous small parcels, sometimes individually fenced."}
{"id": "5c3383d2-775f-4a75-a2be-436eeff2581d", "value": "A building which houses administrative functions relating to local government. Includes directly associated and usually defined grounds."}

{"id": "8406238e-c4d1-4caf-b831-37a77c501f21", "value": "A building which houses administrative functions relating to central government and its agencies. Includes directly associated and usually defined grounds."}
{"id": "b66edf4a-cccc-401a-a591-dcacffc26299", "value": "The offices and directly associated grounds of a Government Department responsible for the administration of the country or a part of it."}
{"id": "e6b181de-5712-4ff7-bfd2-8e19114e655f", "value": "Large road, often multiple carriagewayed, linking significant places."}

{"id": "56f62be6-f5f9-44b7-87f6-5cb2ed4699d6", "value": "An inland body of fresh water. Lakes generally refer to larger examples, ponds to smaller, but there is no clear break along the gradation between the two."}
{"id": "27f7e0ff-fda3-4f42-9732-48520226154b", "value": "An area of freshwater found inland."}

{"id": "36897533-0d3e-4b37-bee5-73f5f2f055d7", "value": "An inland body of fresh water. Ponds generally refer to smaller examples, lakes to larger, but there is no clear break along the gradation between the two. Ponds are often artificial and made for a specific purpose."}
{"id": "14c158b2-54dc-4644-8c0e-8c00d480fe1b", "value": "A channel used for or formed by the conveyance of water."}
{"id": "8171ef0d-8aaf-440e-a06f-f63638291e23", "value": "A shallow lake that is broad in relation to its depth"}
{"id": "d6b79072-dfdb-4919-a5ba-9597907374a8", "value": "Place of Christian worship, usually serving a parish. includes churchyard and immediately related features."}
{"id": "9cd23ca6-9c70-4024-a0bd-a84e1563b4d9", "value": "Place, usually defined, where the dead are carefully and respectfully placed, usually via interment."}

{"id": "e17e4e90-e74c-4eac-8026-82dca9fa6c1d", "value": "Surface workings including shallow shafts, lode workings, open-pit methods and quarrying including some mines of stone, clays, compounds, etc."}
{"id": "7e109183-e26f-4626-9cba-377303bde41b", "value": "A place from which clay is extracted."}

{"id": "cf3df0c0-dd37-4d55-8bb5-9cc8d24aaa96", "value": "Abandoned and/or derelict surface workings such as shallow shafts, lode workings, open-pit methods and quarrying that have subsequently become flooded with water."}
{"id": "19db095d-ab5c-4c73-9718-c757b3598c92", "value": "An excavation open to the sky, caused by the extraction of coal, stone or similar. Use with product type where known."}
{"id": "fdabfcf5-d824-413f-8f65-f2ba7ff9d397", "value": "An excavation on land from which stone or aggregates are extracted for use primarily building and civil engineering."}
{"id": "5cdfcdd3-b977-4f4c-b5b7-5777be583084", "value": "A pit from which marl, a mixture of clay and carbonate of lime, is excavated. Marl is used as a fertilizer."}

{"id": "a005b193-3a1c-428d-a0f2-a004e0c8f310", "value": "An artificial bank or landing place, largely of solid construction, built parallel to, or projecting out from, the shoreline to facilitate the loading and unloading of vessels."}

{"id": "635e926c-bcc2-4ec1-bbcd-b9a9f7b115b0", "value": "A raised platform generally of iron or wood, supported on spaced pillars or props and projecting out into the sea; designed to facilitate the transfer of cargo and/or passengers on and off shipping."}

{"id": "1207c966-4b14-4c8a-a442-19d213daab48", "value": "A structure which protects a beach or harbour by breaking the force of waves. It may be constructed entirely offshore at a strategic location or with one end attached to land. Commonly associated with ports and navigable river mouths."}

{"id": "61008a11-02f6-4057-8b14-1eeb5a409f7a", "value": "Non-military artificial structure designed to counter losses to coastal land from the erosive forces of the sea. May work directly to withstand those forces along a defined line, or they may seek to dissipate them in the inter-tidal zone."}

{"id": "12461d39-4824-4f0e-8d36-bf890607bf5d", "value": "A pier-like structure situated at a harbour entrance or running out into the sea or a lake, whose purpose is often to control tidal flow and sedimentation but may also serve as a berthing point for boats and shipping."}
{"id": "195a1c0d-8019-436e-8269-fd6c14d7dd91", "value": "Secondary woodland whose species are a mix of broadleaved and coniferous trees."}
{"id": "d6579a7c-309f-4553-9bbf-12826806a4c1", "value": "Fields created on the surface of restored land, such as that landscaped from the former dumps of coal mines. Modern and often regular."}
{"id": "660e4dd4-985e-4044-9540-b0ac4ddf07f0", "value": "A central point for the deposit, collection and recycling of waste materials."}
{"id": "905b4fa5-04f8-42d0-a0aa-7211f6beefdd", "value": "A site for burning refuse to ashes using an incinerator."}
{"id": "3eeb9d80-e3ec-4ac6-b76e-f8711082956d", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the disposal of domestic and industrial waste."}
{"id": "963032d8-b7c9-40ba-adf4-c2811befeec7", "value": "An enclosed area of land or garden for the growing of fruit-bearing trees."}

{"id": "cd3e341f-36d4-4c4f-bdbe-ab16276f3f49", "value": "Organised public system, often involving agreed symbols and behaviours, relating humanity to particular beliefs and values. Often links explanatory schemes (for example of the origin and meaning of life) to morality and ethics."}
{"id": "bdb27562-5b6b-44d9-861b-2e99a162b5b7", "value": "Related to respectful disposal of the bodies of the dead."}
{"id": "c268efa1-5a04-4de6-963d-fa325f667f4b", "value": "Helping individuals maintain a satisfactory condition of mind and body, and freedom from sickness, injury and pain."}

{"id": "8045a4f8-0e73-40cc-9be5-8ccd3fc80f26", "value": "Establishment (buildings and directly associated and usually defined grounds) where the community's poor were maintained at public expense, and provided with labour."}

{"id": "cceeae30-0b54-4ee2-8cd1-1bf78ee7bcb0", "value": "Provision of teaching and related material intended to have a formative, and often also a normative effect on the mind, character and abilities of an individual."}
{"id": "38d3fc4e-c926-482b-90ff-78b9a55d0ca7", "value": "An establishment (buildings and directly associated and usually defined grounds) where offenders are confined."}
{"id": "ffb03b23-cdef-4aff-9c83-a6fc867e137c", "value": "-"}

{"id": "51e693b6-4c9e-40e6-851f-48e8088a3e06", "value": "Institutions of government that support civil behaviour or habits of personal living which then cement viable relations between individuals and wider society."}

{"id": "b94fe91d-1711-408a-a094-98c91ba173da", "value": "Land including hunting areas for a monarch or (by invitation) the aristocracy; they usually included large areas of heath, grassland and wetland, that is habitats that supported deer and other game, but also farmland."}
{"id": "0cf16ead-4561-4723-a550-e1afc4a280ad", "value": "Land reclaimed directly from the sea by enclosure and drainage."}
{"id": "30a1b5ea-e4f6-4874-8bfa-9d20ddbb69af", "value": "Land reclaimed directly from wetland."}
{"id": "92ace4f9-3cde-4576-839c-ae39db909d95", "value": "Land reclaimed directly from tidal marsh, usually salt marsh, by enclosure and drainage."}

{"id": "2cdefb2d-29ef-42d3-a574-1b6af8b99917", "value": "Coastal or other low-lying ground taken in for agriculture, usually by dyking and draining. Some medieval (usually smaller more irregular patterns), but mainly post-medieval and modern (larger, rectilinear, and more regular)."}
{"id": "da6dd8f9-0e30-4abb-b84d-b6366d301ae4", "value": "A weekend retreat for parties and others, when hunting in the deer park or forests, or as a viewing station for the chase."}

{"id": "d47963da-6231-4ef2-b6d7-ac258c84dc20", "value": "A place of worship, building and directly associated, often defined, grounds for members of the Society of Friends, a denomination founded by George Fox in c.1650 who believed in pacifist principles and a rejection of the sacrament."}
{"id": "f5621daf-04c8-4c6f-bc30-17deef0c5264", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with ports and docks together with their harbours."}
{"id": "61da48e7-057d-4187-915e-39c52aa81463", "value": "Areas relating to safe passage and route-finding for travel or transport on or in the water, whether inland, coastal or marine."}

{"id": "a7df460a-a1a7-4f50-ac6c-60e6629e4d34", "value": "Features or structures sited at important position-finding or dangerous points on the coast, or on inland waters, for the guidance and warning of mariners."}
{"id": "a27f2482-51a5-4ad3-8fd1-8d362a98742d", "value": "A structure inclined towards the water on which a ship may be built or lowered into the water."}
{"id": "57c84433-87c2-4b24-a96b-08ef1171d1eb", "value": "Areas associated with movement of people or goods on or in water."}
{"id": "b97950b9-3910-4b0f-877e-b2b22cd266e1", "value": "A deposition landform that develops by the process of longshore drift forming a narrow strip of land that juts out into the sea."}

{"id": "65a015f9-5983-4fcc-b478-fe7afd3d61f8", "value": "Coastal areas containing hills or ridges of unconsolidated wind-blown sand. Surfaces of ridges and intervening slacks may be stabilised by surface vegetation. Used for rough grazing."}

{"id": "a08de7e1-ba00-44b6-b0ae-0b3b2e0f7d9d", "value": "The foreshore is broadly equated with land sloping down through the inter-tidal zone from the landward coastal margin; Its extent is defined by perception of the inter-tidal rather than by detailed tidal level definitions."}

{"id": "b9aea4a4-fb93-4191-822a-7fd4ac1bdef1", "value": "The topography at the interface of sea and land, subject to the constant changes in form and perception associated with the tides, the erosive forces of sea and issuing rivers."}
{"id": "4c139181-648c-4ceb-b85c-9d6e39e72a51", "value": "A small inlet on a sea coast or estuary, its sediments often exposed at low tide. Sometimes applied to a river tributary or stream."}
{"id": "3321d224-7083-4a28-bfb8-24a1cb614ff9", "value": "Shallow areas of sand banks, shoals, bars and spits, highly subject to change and extent of low tide exposure due to mobility of sediments."}
{"id": "b96c9ccd-53fa-432b-8393-5d682c2e6146", "value": "A conical, ramped or flat-topped tip of waste discarded from a mine, quarry, clayworks or similar site."}

{"id": "a1105206-1c1e-4bde-b8e1-dcf11f6a7c1c", "value": "Areas used for the disposal of domestic and/or industrial waste. Material deposited may include dredging spoil, drilling waste, treated sewage, domestic refuse and other land waste."}

{"id": "b606474b-e6ce-4708-83e4-ee80a996e687", "value": "An area in the upper inter tidal zone that is sometimes overflowed by the sea and whose vegetation is dominated by salt tolerant herbaceous plants. Saltmarshes are often used for pasture or for collecting water for the production of salt."}

{"id": "8d5d2544-1d9c-43df-88f7-3cd2761f24a5", "value": "An area regularly exploited for commercial fish and/or shellfish extraction; within which the locations of actual fishing activity may vary at any given time, seasonally, according to the species concerned and regulations govening their exploitation."}

{"id": "548d2173-9ef6-472e-b093-66baec05bf5a", "value": "Areas characterised by the regular commercial collection of naturally occurring shellfish stocks for food, bait or other products using a dredge towed behind a fishing vessel. In UK waters the target is usually scallops."}

{"id": "b0edacea-9d15-4d35-9aaa-41ceb8bfef7a", "value": "Areas characterised by commercial fishing using pots or creels which are small portable traps set on the sea floor in coastal waters to catch a variety of crustacea and molluscs. Potting grounds, rarely more than a mile offshore usually on a rocky bottom."}

{"id": "7d719bcb-a111-415f-b339-685b5cfc02d0", "value": "Areas characterised by commercial fishing using large nets that drift in the water, moved by currents and lacking any fixtures to keep them in place. They are rigged in a straight line and are generally used to catch pelagic or migratory species."}

{"id": "37c95e76-284b-4b2c-b1e3-7303a8ffbbae", "value": "Areas characterised by commercial fishing using long line methods; this involves setting out a fishing line, often several kilometers long, from which shorter lines (snoods) are spaced at intervals with baited hooks."}

{"id": "35ef6dbe-bddc-4ba7-a2d9-526012e44eaa", "value": "Areas characterised by commercial fishing using seine nets; which is a long net that hangs in the water column with floats along the upper edge and weights along the bottom. The ends of the net can be drawn together to encircle and herd a school of fish."}

{"id": "8e9d6ac7-1ac2-4cf0-a6b5-e813f3c7e95b", "value": "Activities concerned with the capture or gathering of wild fish and shellfish stocks by various methods such as trawling, netting, trapping, potting, dredging and collection by hand."}

{"id": "3b943375-0046-43a3-a5f0-149c01a809ba", "value": "Areas characterised by commercial fishing using fixed netting or set netting as it is sometimes known. It refers to netting held vertically and stationery in the water column, rather than being towed by a vessel or allowed to drift in the current."}

{"id": "76e446f0-2a05-41ea-b54b-e144f2312a67", "value": "Commercial fishing that involves trawling midwater levels of the water column targeting the pelagic fish species using large funnel shaped nets, held open at the mouth by floats and weights which are towed by one or two (pair trawling) vessels."}

{"id": "986c9dd1-ec1b-4cde-ad41-609c079d91c8", "value": "Areas characterised by the regular commercial collection by hand or hand held tools, of naturally occurring shellfish stocks for food. If collected for bait use BAIT DIGGING AREA and for commercial farming from artificial structures use SHELLFISH FARMING."}

{"id": "37e7572c-0132-4ed9-9b6f-1200030d026c", "value": "Commercial fishing that involves trawling the lowest levels of the water column and/or the surface of the sea floor. These methods often result in disturbance to the sea floor itself."}

{"id": "d1f1ca2e-7369-4dc9-b94b-1d656e3c3972", "value": "A purpose built building and associated grounds, usually owned and operated by a local authority, where people go to keep fit or relax through using the facilities."}

{"id": "c9cc06e4-381f-4cc8-a526-77ccbf2f16ae", "value": "The long-established historic centre of a town or city, typically delineated in historic characterisation as extent shown on an early epoch of OS mapping."}
{"id": "38f4846e-e92f-413d-b17e-0f2d6737daa4", "value": "Extension of town or city beyond the Historic Urban Core, usually as defined by extents shown on early epoch OS mapping."}
{"id": "34d59f82-de95-4c3e-b07f-b016bbb8cffd", "value": "-"}
{"id": "56dc260b-c367-45ea-a22c-9d8fffa00961", "value": "Urban area dominated by housing."}
{"id": "8c47ec4a-9f0c-4efe-a079-ce4923e7c9fd", "value": "Communication of information by wire, radio, electrical and digital means."}
{"id": "605e97b3-1476-48d2-af71-58e4d22218a1", "value": "A terrestrial or submarine insulated cable or pipe along which telecommunication data is passed."}
{"id": "22030c8f-d523-4d5b-800f-3ad92cc4def7", "value": "A complex of buildings and other structures (and directly related grounds) used to transmit information via telecommunication systems."}
{"id": "ce0695ce-1f33-4c66-92c0-b298e86f8543", "value": "Power generation by releasing stored water through a turbine driving a generator."}
{"id": "03ec44f5-5d08-4b21-98e5-745d035166e8", "value": "Buildings and grounds of secondary or tertiary educational establishments, below the status of universities."}

{"id": "7c838b59-de94-4805-9b7f-469f70432dc8", "value": "A place from which lead ore is mined. Includes closely associated spoil, processing, and transport facilities. Also use MINE and other ores extracted where relevant, eg. SILVER MINE."}
{"id": "d5b59d0c-022f-4a76-9f8b-6d4cb3953f0c", "value": "A building where people pay to see films and 'moving pictures'."}
{"id": "98c658ee-4e7e-4aea-8ab6-c2a5f9b921d5", "value": "A complex, including large covered areas, used for housing public displays."}
{"id": "02948bb2-e030-4156-b895-a225de375970", "value": "Complex designed to accomodate major gatherings."}
{"id": "66fc436b-6d43-4694-94a5-a72ce2b2e6ee", "value": "A large area, usually open-air, used for permanent, seasonal or regular shows, events or exhibitions."}

{"id": "765150b9-7218-49a1-9d36-76da1eeee1d0", "value": "An artificial lake or pond, often made by damming a stream, whose main function is to catch the eye and to contribute to ornamentally designed landscapes. As such a common feature of landscape parks."}

{"id": "081b973b-36fd-4022-86bf-ca2fad63eb7a", "value": "Extensive grounds, usually associated with a country house, laid out (with tree plantations, shrubs and often adjusted with earth movement) so as to produce a perception of broad unmanaged and often unpeopled vistas."}

{"id": "a2de67a8-2556-4589-b510-c06c81c03713", "value": "A hilltop enclosure bounded by one or more substantial banks, ramparts and ditches. Now forming a feature within other landscape character types such as recreation, rough ground or enclosed land."}
{"id": "90844f10-d362-4285-8f03-34d3e74662f1", "value": "Areas of furze divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "f6f24063-0bf3-4896-9274-18a57e521744", "value": "A straight road lined with trees along either side, also straight lines of trees found in parkland usually leading to a landscape feature."}

{"id": "1ea8c178-ca07-4c98-a7a4-68277d32a01f", "value": "A holding's fields contained within two long, usually perfectly straight boundaries extending outwards from a farmstead; often parallel, but sometimes splayed. Divided by cross boundaries into fields. Usually post-medieval or modern."}
{"id": "dff4e7b8-5fd9-4f8b-b9db-c16dd3884792", "value": "Area designed to accommodate several businesses, usually non-industrial, but normally not exclusively retail."}

{"id": "e0395ed9-5590-4421-bf24-e509b6ac4b68", "value": "Fields established within former parkland, either medieval deer park or post-medieval landscaped park. Tend to be large and regular fields and land often retains some parkland features, notably standard trees."}

{"id": "0a8ca5ef-b47d-4848-b386-690034deaae4", "value": "Field system, usually with perfectly straight boundaries, usually rectilinear and regular, developed by reorganisation by several landowners of an earlier system. Term often used for post-medieval non-Parliamentary Enclosure of open fields."}
{"id": "7e9362dd-6ff9-4c66-a490-1363a75eba01", "value": "Facilities provided for indoor recreation, often with external grounds associated (car parks etc)."}

{"id": "2b743b0b-1b77-439d-abc2-e34a64cc3884", "value": "A medicinal or mineral spring often with an associated building and directly associated grounds. Often found closely grouped, around which settlements and spa towns have developed."}
{"id": "640f1c8f-6df6-4142-8b7f-45d86fcc4474", "value": "An area or place for recreation, typically with electronic game machines and gambling machines."}
{"id": "a50879b4-1fa3-499a-b27a-cf8de9b2755f", "value": "An area of buildings, artificial ponds and/or tanks in which aquatic plants and animals are kept for observaton and study as recreation."}

{"id": "b2b2625c-ac9e-460e-a17c-7d9c04e622dd", "value": "Peat deposits comprise unconsolidated semi-carbonised plant remains formed in freshwater-saturated environments. The type referred to here are those formed in earlier periods and may be exposed by erosion on the land, inter-tidal or sea-floor surface."}

{"id": "8a9c40ac-fae7-43ec-b842-0b93dc0cb8f5", "value": "An area of fenland that has become overgrown with trees or shrubs. Normally the result of natural succession, and thus regarded as a form of ancient woodland."}

{"id": "7ebfadf1-4016-4cd9-8c55-e0d32e4ae55b", "value": "An area whose soil is saturated with moisture either permanently or on an intermittent cycle eg. fens, marshes and peat bogs. The dominant vegetation of wetlands varies enormously and the vegetation cover may be broken by areas of open water."}

{"id": "75cafda7-cebd-4779-b875-7ce28a3345f1", "value": "Poorly drained land, can include uplands with extensive blanket bog or low-lying damp unimproved ground. Used for rough grazing, occasionally for hay-making, and where peat was cut as a source of turf for domestic fuel."}
{"id": "4e390f0f-3a48-44d7-8720-9331b0a8cfde", "value": "A wetland type that accumulates acidic peat. Sometimes named 'moss'."}

{"id": "beb902ad-cdfd-4f9a-abff-b98140a8840f", "value": "Areas characterised by the commercial cultivation of fish populations under controlled conditions. These areas may be sited in inland or be coastally located artificial ponds, or in rivers, estuaries and the open sea and enclosed in tanks, cages or nets."}

{"id": "7c2a39f5-a03b-43b3-a4e4-4685f08e36c0", "value": "The commercial cultivation of fish and shellfish populations under controlled conditions, often enclosed from wild stocks. It includes the raising of saltwater and/or freshwater species and may occur both inland or in fully marine situations."}

{"id": "db1d4edc-db48-4783-ab7a-fdc0784d5c88", "value": "Areas chacterised by the commercial cultivation of shellfish populations under controlled conditions, sometimes enclosed from wild stocks. Shellfish farming includes oyster, mussel and cockle beds which are seeded and managed over several seasons."}

{"id": "258eaee5-d876-41a1-aa52-71140ea66d57", "value": "A building or group of buildings, often surrounded by a system of fortifications, used as a residential and training site by members of an armed force."}

{"id": "09765a08-2636-4acc-bb45-7e84181b391f", "value": "The principal church of a diocese in which the cathedra or bishop's throne is to be found. Includes precinct and immediately related features."}
{"id": "7d629327-74f4-47d6-aa1e-27e9f5ed7593", "value": "A piece of ground, or a building, on which artillery may be fired at targets during training or exercises.."}
{"id": "ec175791-7011-4759-bda5-ed39d9df110a", "value": "A building or site incorporating radar equipment used for detecting the presence of enemy aircraft or ships."}

{"id": "e0d91015-ad8a-4a01-be28-3027e761fb6a", "value": "Route regularly used by ships engaged in commerce or trade. May be defined by usage or in some areas, formally defined by regulation. Distinguished from the Navigation route Sub-character Type by the association with commerical shipping."}
{"id": "da86b9fa-970e-4aab-9f82-735703388ad4", "value": "Upland rough ground left open, not divided by stock-proof boundaries."}

{"id": "860ca916-098a-4ca5-b04a-a574db1a8a5a", "value": "An area from which sediments have been removed to ensure a safe depth of water in channels and berths for navigational purposes or to mitigate risk of flooding or protect a sensitive habitat."}

{"id": "c815fcdc-74ce-410a-8fd8-08f1508a8864", "value": "Land with peat soil, such as an active or former bog, the peat often cut for domestic fuel, the land often seasonally grazed. Often known as a 'moss'."}
{"id": "8aeb6f95-b028-456e-8587-52be37d7d38d", "value": "Unimproved farmland, used primarily for grazing, where the vegetation is dominated by grasses and other herbaceous plants."}

{"id": "cd78ed09-e70b-44c0-b26a-5f859db774af", "value": "Area dominated by rough vegetation, with no visible evidence of recent agricultural improvement. Used primarily for grazing and, historically, fuel gathering, often in common."}

{"id": "7618fb52-3cb4-4083-bfae-fe35f4b2d914", "value": "Unimproved, but grazed area of low-growing woody shrubby vegetation, including heathers and gorses, sometimes in a mosaic with grassland and damp areas."}

{"id": "fb19b72d-f3f1-4176-9e0a-5daeb9fa8782", "value": "Unenclosed land, such as wasteland, forest or pasture, owned by an estate, but over which tenants and sometimes certain others have rights (pasture, turbary, estovers, pannage, etc)."}
{"id": "7f9ee63f-c702-483d-9c52-27f6dab94d8b", "value": "Unimproved land dominated by furze (gorse), used for rough grazing and harvested as domestic fuel."}

{"id": "37c7fb49-da9a-494c-a5f4-c52a214bef2e", "value": "Area of often grassy ground, usually common, normally situated at the centre of a village or hamlet, sometimes within or near a town. Usually maintained by grazing."}
{"id": "30f5c25e-4cf3-41f6-94e4-c774f5a2f328", "value": "Chalk grassland left open, undivided by stock-proof boundaries."}

{"id": "515ca375-35e0-47f4-aa37-12a12838ce27", "value": "A large building, often with directly associated and usually defined grounds, used for the transaction of the public business of a city, the holding of courts of justice, entertainments and other activities."}
{"id": "1c833934-a10e-4855-a44d-b64773dba073", "value": "A building or complex often with several buildings where municipal offices and other public buildings are situated."}
{"id": "c8442342-afe1-4816-b789-89379b9fb1be", "value": "Place (buildings and directly associated, usually defined, grounds) of Islamist or Mohammedan worship."}

{"id": "fc3dc99d-cbd2-421c-adb6-712d05d94ae2", "value": "Place of Christian worship; can include non-conformist (and non-parochial) churches (q.v.) and privately owned chapels. Includes immediately associated and usually physically defined land."}

{"id": "375afca5-1b12-4a50-a91a-dca093c5486f", "value": "A place (buildings and directly associated and usually defined grounds) where appropriate acts, rites and ceremonies are performed to honour or revere a supernatural being, power or holy entity. Use specific type where known."}
{"id": "5261b5c6-0e36-4389-88a8-58a7ba59c650", "value": "Place of worship (buildings and directly associated and usually defined grounds) for communities of Jews."}
{"id": "ec98edd0-5c6f-42b6-ac79-7fabccde19d6", "value": "-"}
{"id": "b9608929-77c8-4b10-8e2e-a35f78297609", "value": "Areas dominated by activity relating directly to the building, use, maintenance, storage and administration of shipping and boats.."}

{"id": "cff3b5b9-6c43-45e6-a78e-2730327afb91", "value": "Covers industries applying various processes to primary materials to prepare them for use either directly or in manufacturing industry. Use specific type where known."}

{"id": "901c94c2-a3c5-4f94-a55f-1eea27169f16", "value": "Production of secondary materials through various processes; distinguished from PROCESSING INDUSTRY\u00c2\u00bfs preparation of primary materials."}
{"id": "8c506bfa-5ecf-410e-8f54-aebd1810f2ae", "value": "-"}

{"id": "cab9e06a-2824-4ab8-b633-1dadedcdd2dc", "value": "An area of land owned by a developer, whether a private entrepreneur or a public authority, and divided into plots for leasing or sale to manufacturing or commercial concerns which may share some common services."}
{"id": "4820459a-ec59-4ed1-b846-e4df53b6b08d", "value": "Ornamental gardens, usually open to the public, that take advantage of the peculiar topography and climate found on cliffs."}
{"id": "63857b2f-f451-493b-bdfa-a5cdedd4f46d", "value": "An area of rolling upland terrain characterised by chalk escarpments separated by vales of softer earth."}
{"id": "b209bf54-11c9-4f00-b0a4-9df29e6c32c5", "value": "An area of elevated ground. As it is a relative term, the altitude of uplands can vary greatly."}
{"id": "52e2fc39-41b5-4c5d-ae80-a6d92776d9ec", "value": "A rock outcrop exposed and shaped by weathering, usually found at or near the summit of a hill."}

{"id": "bf69358d-ab65-4cb6-9567-c2b242ca0cee", "value": "Rural settlement in which farmsteads are typically clustered together, normally as villages (and especially in the central province), but also as hamlets. Can also refer to a single nucleated settlement."}
{"id": "dba5c3fa-7227-4fa0-9415-5124c29f6477", "value": "Linear arrangement of farmsteads and dwellings, usually built along a road."}

{"id": "87575428-c2e3-482a-95d2-c86acf8ff5e6", "value": "Collection of farmsteads, dwellings, yards, gardens etc. Larger than hamlet, smaller than town. Often includes church, inn, shops, workshops, manor house. Main rural settlement form in central province; rarer elsewhere. Also industrial villages."}
{"id": "0771a034-16e5-403d-87e2-7668c95d57de", "value": "Small settlement with no ecclesiastical or lay administrative function and usually with no other amenities."}
{"id": "b169cdd0-bea4-4d55-ac8c-52ac44e2ac91", "value": "A common used for the resting and grazing of herds cattle being 'driven' to and from market."}

{"id": "d8028265-54f9-4881-85ea-9a25d043267f", "value": "An area, usually immediately adjacent to a beach with numerous small timber one-roomed dwellings or shelters where holiday makers could rest after a day spent sunbathing, swimming and playing on the beach."}
{"id": "f1fb9ac5-1cc3-447b-9d5a-f77efbe2d354", "value": "Place (building and grounds) where the dead are respectfully incinerated and remembered."}
{"id": "853d30fd-9438-467f-ba15-6b04643be254", "value": "Moorland divided by stock-proof boundaries."}

{"id": "4366faca-511f-4b52-ac80-bc22544fe76f", "value": "Plantations containing both broadleaved and coniferous trees, including areas of planting, ground ripping, immature or mature stands, felled areas."}
{"id": "3200bdd9-045f-4cae-985a-8dd6a560b540", "value": "Areas of the water column and/or sea surface above sea floor hazards and in a buffered zone around them."}
{"id": "da256700-be0d-4e83-8d0b-5690f9714e8a", "value": "Farmstead with no near neighbours, usually an element of a dispersed settlement pattern."}

{"id": "43a58a84-2395-4376-8578-f3953743a3b2", "value": "A planned residential area, usually with its own self-contained street system including cul-de-sacs, sometimes with its own amenities, such as shops, a public house etc."}
{"id": "40595d95-83c1-4737-a716-5fcf2f1916ce", "value": "Rural residence with no immediate neighbours."}

{"id": "59fbf31e-8ea6-48c0-bcf5-1af92b90ded2", "value": "A naval base that builds, repairs, docks or converts warships and is manned by civilian engineers and workers and administered by engineer duty officers."}

{"id": "acd18bca-2018-4bc5-8dfc-632f4c4f073e", "value": "Large multiple carriageway for fast-moving motor traffic, continuing for long distances without traffic intersections and subject to legally specified 'motorway regulations'."}

{"id": "0ac8bd84-bc49-4453-b169-de0e1958deb5", "value": "The course or channel of a river or stream preserved as a geological or geomorphological feature. Use for areas containing individual examples or an individual system. For areas of inter-fluvial ridges & other features, use 'Palaeolandscape component'."}
{"id": "730404e9-35e1-4be3-a62b-4c1e21e4127b", "value": "Agricultural village with farmsteads and cottages wholly or mainly arranged along the edge of a common."}
{"id": "b85085a2-1c51-4f59-bd5c-855b7942ce2b", "value": "A significant watercourse largely following the natural drainage pattern and flowing towards another river, a lake or the sea."}
{"id": "f437cf23-cda9-4d52-a70a-a65ae81a5d79", "value": "Moorland left open, not divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "48481bcc-6879-4125-8814-c9f4f6eaf780", "value": "Areas of furze left open, not divided by stock-proof boundaries."}

{"id": "b439b658-9577-4e13-8108-2a38b3786f5c", "value": "An area dominated by rocks rising from the general level of the seabed and breaking the sea surface at some or all states of the tide, posing a risk for navigation."}

{"id": "69e99284-e119-4407-b07c-d91368c75a8e", "value": "Field pattern of any type or date that has been subject to revision, through either insertion or removal of boundaries, but where the original form is still legible."}

{"id": "99cf2fbf-aebc-46ff-90ab-b666da565831", "value": "Patterns of very large fields, some with boundaries over 1km long. Usually resulting from post WW2 combination of holdings & the removal of earlier boundaries creating land units convenient for highly mechanised arable, or for extensive livestock raising"}

{"id": "bc5dfa05-14cf-4d1f-98d8-969307ebc85e", "value": "Enlarged fields, created by the amalgamation by boundary removal of smaller fields, mainly since the 19th century and usually since the Second World War. Usually to ease mechanised working and increase productivity."}

{"id": "a9857c50-ccc4-4ca4-bc01-9946d36b0dd3", "value": "Marginal fields, often part of open field systems, beyond the more closely assessed and more intensively worked infields. In places left uncultivated for many decades. Often worked in common and divided into strips."}
{"id": "0e94ec57-46f8-4c7b-9340-7a332fbeddfc", "value": "An enclosed field for horses. Usually a modern adaptation of part of an early field system."}

{"id": "1307dc14-154d-4dab-ade4-bf862c18bce1", "value": "A group or complex of fields which appear to form a coherent whole, usually on the basis of another system, normally that of tenure. Includes rearrangements of earlier systems."}
{"id": "5fdfd9a8-4ce4-42f3-a162-6314e11376c6", "value": "The more closely assessed and more intensively worked fields of an infield-outfield system, usually of open field type."}

{"id": "97b77384-69e9-4e00-adf0-c95595101e88", "value": "Heathland used for the shooting of Red Grouse. Managed, by the controlled burning of areas of heather, to create a habitat that is favourable to grouse. Lines of butts used by the shooters are a common feature."}
{"id": "046cf35e-16bc-4877-9fb8-3bbe896e9353", "value": "Buildings and yards in which dogs and hunting hounds are kept and exercised."}

{"id": "a2748654-71dd-4d40-a523-3dcd494cdd37", "value": "A large, enclosed park, often containing some woodland and divided to provide a variety of habitats for shelter, grazing etc for deer, usually fallow, for hunting and for aesthetic appreciation.."}
{"id": "75a36780-b924-4567-9e38-5615dc55b1cb", "value": "Land primarily devoted to the persuit, trapping, shooting and hunting of wild or purposefully raised animals."}
{"id": "8518dbd4-286a-4499-9c5c-d0e35c1b4055", "value": "A power station used to produce electricity, fired by coal gas."}
{"id": "b84c11cd-8ea5-420e-b44b-2613bbbbaeb1", "value": "An industrial complex for large-scale production of iron."}

{"id": "2e40f017-bf2c-4f92-9859-f20f5d3afb11", "value": "Area of ancient fields whose boundaries are either curving or sinuous and whose shapes do not conform to a regular pattern. Often seen to have developed by sequential accretion of individual enclosures and by ad hoc subdivision."}
{"id": "f83b2c42-f046-4d6a-b22d-ec9050a1abf5", "value": "A site where cobalt is mined. Includes closely associated spoil, processing and transport facilities."}
{"id": "0d4934cf-292d-43c7-8858-8f6f95171516", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the harnessing the energy of wave power for electrical power generation."}

{"id": "78f1ad96-4dd0-4fcc-bbd9-f13aa04b18ef", "value": "Structures where electrical energy is generated by conversion from continually replenished energy flows in the natural environment, such as sunlight, wind, rain, tides, waves, etc."}
{"id": "73bd9c0e-eabb-44ce-af37-51e1d583e1f7", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the generation of electricity by utilising the power of the tide."}
{"id": "2ff5bfde-ff31-4e9f-9957-76a0770296d4", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the generation of electricity by harnessing the energy of the wind."}
{"id": "ac3f277c-aaa6-4d9c-abc9-45126f989760", "value": "Primary and secondary educational establishments, buildings and directly associated and usually defined grounds, including car parking etc."}
{"id": "1e0731e4-2874-4815-810f-2edb5c08ab3c", "value": "Spieces-rich grazed land on chalk geology."}
{"id": "a5e60d0e-bf4f-4110-aa97-baa7471d50b8", "value": "A place where ships or boats are built, repaired and moored."}
{"id": "be0a8006-082d-478c-a7a1-64ad564e6d0f", "value": "A place where silver is extracted. Use with other minerals extracted and MINE where relevant, eg. LEAD MINE."}

{"id": "534e0db6-4716-4273-bc89-7ca2e6ff2ce0", "value": "Farmland, whose predominant character developed since World War 2. Usually broad-brush characterisation that includes farming settlement and various land use."}
{"id": "e746c26b-eb18-4ade-9c40-f70f06bc8a3b", "value": "Patterns of fields that took in farmland (either cultivated or improved grassland) from other land uses."}

{"id": "506a3dd5-b2ba-4360-ade1-6b1c6ecede0f", "value": "Permanent grassland, usually enclosed with stock-proof boundaries. Low-lying and damp or hard by farmstead, receiving yard dung. Ideally lush, and mown for hay. Also secure convenient grazing for young or sickly livestock. Common or individually held."}

{"id": "5a0fc80c-566c-4f9b-b090-431ebf02a300", "value": "Field patterns with perfectly straight stock-proof boundaries, usually rectilinear and regular. Normally produced by planned enclosure by several landholders of formerly open or common land. Usually post medieval or modern."}
