{"id": "58be32db-22e1-4cac-a24d-d2fe1617bc90", "value": "A designated area of water in which the performance of submarines can be evaluated and where crews can practice."}

{"id": "b7ae1727-2566-4b8e-ac58-d845a6de131c", "value": "A purpose-built, or modified, building and directly associated grounds for organisations and associations to meet for presentations and consultation."}
{"id": "f8932421-31c9-459d-bddc-db39940cea58", "value": "Upland rough ground divided by stock-proof boundaries."}
{"id": "e017ad43-d820-417c-b135-5c440b59eb6a", "value": "Upland area with rough vegetation created and maintained by grazing, often seasonal, and historically by fuel collection."}
{"id": "33cf1840-8e09-4ce7-a12a-546a4aff996f", "value": "Tracts of submerged land retaining macrofossil evidence, often in situ, for former woodland and other woody vegetation cover."}

{"id": "01228f9a-904b-433c-9517-dde065ee8dbd", "value": "Relates to surviving areas of ancient topographic features of former exposed land with evidence or strong potential for associated palaeo-environmental deposits and/or old land surfaces."}
{"id": "2852c5f0-f2f4-4f87-9f53-7f7c831c32a2", "value": "An industrial manufacturing complex producing bricks."}
{"id": "b4976ab9-5d05-4536-b1bc-6ce421f92c12", "value": "An area from which oil produced by geological processes is extracted from deep beneath the earth's surface."}
{"id": "2e005f62-369a-4f06-aca6-290796d64ced", "value": "A supporting structure for drilling machinery used in the extraction of, or prospecting for, natural gas."}

{"id": "5144771a-118c-489a-8c7f-b8e91eaa6c34", "value": "An area of water adjacent to a port or harbour, falling under the jurisdiction of a port/harbour authority. Includes associated traffic areas and restricted navigation areas."}

{"id": "e9c88897-3ab5-4027-a836-effeaf99f136", "value": "An area of the coast where ships can find shelter or safe anchorage. Harbours require features, natural or artificial that provide shelter and a pool area large and deep enough to accommodate vessels at anchor."}

{"id": "cc2eae73-120b-4d53-b593-2a6d923476df", "value": "An area of sea or coast where vessels anchor, often provided by sheltered conditions afforded by the topography of the nearby coast. They are often located along coastlines within bays or areas sheltered from prevailing winds and/or strong currents."}

{"id": "f4e412f6-54de-4989-9901-58764e75eb1e", "value": "Buildings made chiefly of glass, in which plants and fruit are germinated, brought on and sometimes grown to maturity. Often grouped on land with a favourable aspect."}
{"id": "295f70a9-65c4-4247-91f3-e222747f639e", "value": "A garden devoted to the growth of vegetables, for either domestic use or sale."}
{"id": "8502e23a-4c56-423d-a96a-04060830f321", "value": "An area of land used to grow vegetables, fruit and flowers to be sold at markets."}

{"id": "d6b74bc5-a59b-4007-8531-5ab16dce519e", "value": "An enclosed piece of land, generally large in area, usually either surrounding a country house or castle, or conveniently adjacent to it. Used for hunting, the cultivation of trees, pasture and visual enjoyment."}

{"id": "d2ce364a-8657-4aac-b9c4-c6def4f22ee9", "value": "A group of planted trees or shrubs, designed to enhance the landscape, often by obscuring eyescores or by framing preferred views. A common feature of landscape parks."}

{"id": "edf07f37-e258-4cc4-b00e-e31c94a4199c", "value": "Approach or drive within an aornamentally designed landscape marked by carefully planted trees, sometimes also by banks or walls. Often comprises one or more straight lines with a house or other feature displayed at one end."}
{"id": "70dd7a73-b380-4cb2-86a5-d087c84a57d5", "value": "A plantation of trees or shrubs usually linear in plan placed to provide shelter from the wind for parks and gardens."}
{"id": "4fadc647-0837-4d4d-8c6b-d0059ed237f5", "value": "The entire playing area and associated buildings upon which the game of cricket is played and where spectators pay to watch."}
{"id": "7b77c6b3-a846-4387-bc37-2bea30f94529", "value": "An industrial complex involved in the production of chemicals."}

{"id": "e3616123-bb72-4964-9f3c-cca7785be852", "value": "A regular commercial passenger route across an area of sea, estuary, river or lake, or an area of port, dock or harbour. Includes chain link ferry crossings."}
{"id": "9e0e279f-bfb7-43ba-97e8-f8e4bdb0594f", "value": "A mine used for the extraction of tungsten-bearing ore. Use with other mineral ores extracted and MINE, eg. TIN MINE."}
{"id": "89a445db-bc78-4ce0-9041-73b8816f973e", "value": "Area designed for retailing, often at the edge of an urban area convenient for private transport."}
{"id": "34a3737d-ec74-4f34-989b-a6f7cae49cad", "value": "A place, buildings and directly associated grounds, where gardening tools, plants, etc, are sold."}
{"id": "08b979d0-1190-445b-ae5c-67f68258f277", "value": "Being in a state of busily undertaking commercially viable work; being a body undertaking such business."}
{"id": "8e9507f3-d5cc-4297-8dd7-0238ee5b614d", "value": "A building and its directly associated grounds, used for the accommodation of paying travellers and guests."}
{"id": "238cff3a-4ed2-48ce-bd94-649c35bf4d67", "value": "Facilities (buildings and directly associated grounds) for the storage of goods."}
{"id": "95aeb541-4618-40e2-9afe-88cdfa741436", "value": "An open space or covered building(s) to which livestock, goods, etc, are brought and displayed for sale."}
{"id": "5597b32f-b3ba-405f-9697-3fca5e8a9ab9", "value": "Street (often with associated back yards etc) predominantly fitted with retail outlets."}
{"id": "2973ba98-e284-49eb-bd29-1b271d852a22", "value": "A place from which iron ore is mined. Includes closely associated spoil, processing, and transport facilities."}
{"id": "1eee4ae7-0c1b-4c5c-b714-ee6ecc386624", "value": "Large structures built alongside the water's edge where ships may lie for unloading."}
{"id": "059ea5e7-521a-4a15-9035-517504f233fd", "value": "A coal-burning power station where domestic electricity for an area is produced, eg. Drax Power Station near the Humber Estuary."}
{"id": "b53b1157-7de3-4dc6-9748-e0c5b8d17aaf", "value": "Buildings found at the site of a mine at the point where underground workings meet the surface."}

{"id": "8b3066d9-526c-4c20-9492-75165fcd9884", "value": "An excavation made in the earth for the purpose of digging out metallic ores, coal, salt, or precious stones etc. Use specific type where known."}

{"id": "73b6222c-329b-4816-9e8f-1c0bace12563", "value": "A building or set of buildings and structures where power, especially electrical or mechanical, is generated. Use more specific type where known."}

{"id": "09ccdb0c-7eea-4b97-9740-3f2d5fbd801c", "value": "An electricity-producing power station fired by oil."}

{"id": "50c84007-7684-4703-8b0d-e8efb0f0ab16", "value": "Areas dominated by commercial complex(es) encompassing lightly-built holidaymaker's accommodation and associated facilities, sometimes including entertainment areas."}

{"id": "1cca07d4-19f8-45e1-a4d2-6a13625c76ab", "value": "A planned town built to disperse population following the Second World War, largely under the powers of the New Towns Act 1946. Normally not actually new, but developed around existing settlements that form historic urban cores."}

{"id": "10d9b6ba-7bea-46cc-8c1f-2d9056cde459", "value": "Areas characterised by the extraction of sand and gravel by dredging from the sea floor, for use principally in construction and civil engineering. Also includes associated onshore facilities such as wharves, and aggregates processing areas."}

{"id": "7ac7a9f1-813b-40c8-8c28-8648307c7fdb", "value": "Areas of excavation from which sand and gravel are obtained for use principally in construction and civil engineering. Includes directly associated facilities for aggregates processing."}
{"id": "741d1abc-de13-484f-a006-2a8b2c7f58de", "value": "Buildings and structures associated with road transport."}

{"id": "810a492a-3a05-472e-9b1a-5d0b15029fa8", "value": "Artificial constructions used to prevent water flooding the surrounding area. Often taking the form of a bank or wall but may be more elaborate (eg the Thames Barrier) and include run-off drains and reservoirs."}
{"id": "65a97389-c978-4e2f-a395-7876a2afb7bc", "value": "A place where smaller vessels are built, repaired and stored"}

{"id": "62b8c82d-4a8f-4991-a4b2-69ea94b3e7d8", "value": "An area of wet or dry docks, storage areas and workshops for the building, repair, fitting, loading and unloading of ships and therefore situated on a sea coast or estuary."}
{"id": "48257c4d-5679-4c54-bbe7-62968cdcd886", "value": "Buildings, sites and structures associated with the construction and repair of ships and boats."}
{"id": "37c16b13-c1cf-43b9-8675-93df60d40ddf", "value": "Areas dominated by use for recreational fishing and angling."}
{"id": "7e1595a4-b463-4ca0-97c4-e8bd5b3486a2", "value": "Heathland left open, not divided by stock-proof boundaries."}

{"id": "75fa515c-2fbf-40e1-9330-1d6ece35a14c", "value": "A bog that develops in gently sloping valleys upon a peat layer. Valley bogs may develop in relatively dry and warm climates, but because they rely on ground or surface water, they only occur on acidic substrates."}

{"id": "87891f0a-1767-426c-96fc-30ea475f41f5", "value": "Defensive structures, obstacles like concrete cubes, cylinders or pimples against invading tanks that were erected in the defence of Britain during the Second World War."}
{"id": "11033de7-ab52-4752-b86e-6c78b8f1199e", "value": "Taking pleasure from the particular qualities and facilities afforded by or established at the sea and coast."}
{"id": "99341e67-d4fc-45c6-81ad-85c2f01d11c6", "value": "Activities undertaken in leisure (or discretionary) time for the purposes of enjoyment, amusement or pleasure."}

{"id": "1abc7b2f-f1d2-406a-8c47-75f0fdf54dca", "value": "A piece of ground over which small arms or large artillery may be fired at targets during training or exercises. Firing ranges regularly form components of much larger military practice areas."}

{"id": "11e6dc9e-d72c-42e7-b4ab-b97b421ae2f5", "value": "An area of sea across which naval ships fire artillery at target sites or areas. In some cases accompanied by land-based observation facilities housing equipment to record accuracy and damage."}
{"id": "7fd49577-02be-4281-8afb-b1680f1ac875", "value": "A target range used for rifle and small arms practice."}
{"id": "b7c5815e-8373-4d31-9ac4-92024580a1c0", "value": "A mine used for the extraction of zinc-bearing ore. Use with other metal ores extracted and MINE where necessary, eg. LEAD MINE."}
{"id": "b3a9188d-15e3-4116-968d-1c99c3d54921", "value": "An industrial complex for large-scale production of steel in the 19th and 20th centuries."}

{"id": "85a3715e-ccb1-4ad9-9926-b012fc248bda", "value": "Areas whose character is dominated by regular digging to acquire bait for fishing by various methods. Generally found in estuaries, sandy and rocky foreshores."}

{"id": "1d16e1d6-032f-4297-a8ca-b33cf1691560", "value": "Ancient woodland where original natural tree coverage has been clear-felled (often during the 20th century world wars) and the area replanted with other trees, often coniferous."}
{"id": "dc2bc8fb-cd9e-4f4e-8733-999eafe0db06", "value": "A way suitable for wheeled transport."}

{"id": "1cafc178-f7e6-494a-b5b4-82fd311bba32", "value": "A building, room or suite of rooms where books, or other materials, are classified by subject and stored for use by the library's members. Includes directly associated and usually defined grounds."}

{"id": "1fe95f32-ff12-43e3-b31c-a81e07f0736f", "value": "A largely residential area within a town or city usually situated away from its centre, often in medieval towns outwith any town walls. {"id": "19c14293-a1a6-4e06-bfcc-186a9c0786db", "value": "Sites and structures associated with the storage and distribution of water."}

{"id": "e1ebec7b-fcbb-48b7-bb55-24199f37e151", "value": "Provision of structures to remove, reduce or mitigate the risk of coastal, riverine and/or estuarine flooding from the sea, rivers or unchannelled rainfall run-off or to counter losses to coastal land from maritime erosive forces."}

{"id": "b150beeb-b54e-4f6c-803d-70abe138c602", "value": "Obstacles placed in open spaces and alongside roads designed to prevent the successful landing of enemy airborne forces; usually of Second World War date."}
{"id": "fd8c0d4b-f53b-4400-b571-c916e33aa083", "value": "An area where osiers (types of willows, producing long straight stems) are cultivated for use in basketry."}
{"id": "138b1c5f-f378-4ae8-b7bb-f1d53117f353", "value": "A building in which works of art are displayed, permanently or temporarily."}

{"id": "0618f766-d373-406d-9915-70faf88d056f", "value": "A building, group of buildings or space within a building, where objects of value such as works of art, antiquities, scientific specimens, or other artefacts are housed, conserved and displayed. Includes directly associated and usually defined grounds."}
{"id": "c82c8157-247a-4698-b48b-ec060f66b34d", "value": "Sites, buildings and structures associated with the defence of the British Isles against invasion from seaborne or airborne forces."}
{"id": "a98bba19-7935-4f9a-8a18-d64a7643e580", "value": "An area of ground or water containing explosive mines. In controlled minefields, also includes areas containing the controlling sites."}
{"id": "90704b9a-1f34-4642-bfc5-dcca88c82d46", "value": "Ancient woodland where original natural tree coverage has been replanted with other trees, often coniferous."}

{"id": "6a2c0e0f-c05e-4318-9fb0-e47ccfc79824", "value": "A Roman period, permanently fortified military base incorporating a range of barracks, victualling and command structures. Often built to standardised plans which developed through time."}
{"id": "9750966d-0ccb-4d6c-b342-a4f32112a040", "value": "A mine yielding rock salt extracted either as rock salt or pumped out as brine."}
{"id": "8d59a6c7-1d0d-471b-b542-9b61abe2d00a", "value": "A water filled hollow caused by subsidence resulting from subterranean industrial extraction, for example coal mining and salt extraction."}
{"id": "be887672-ea3d-4023-8d29-b89e9e4ac2e2", "value": "A works where crude oil is distilled into its fractions or cuts."}
{"id": "11ebb48b-6116-469d-addb-0f9a20c1e763", "value": "A purpose-built facility for racing motor cars and/or motor cycles which may also include grandstands or concourses."}
{"id": "aa01cd41-40b4-4bf5-a6f8-b08073d49831", "value": "A place where vessels can land passengers and goods"}

{"id": "450bcaa0-0ac8-4df9-b3da-ce89da5d6fdc", "value": "A plot of land longer than it is wide, usually running perpendicularly from street with dwelling on street front. The holding of a burgess, and thus typical of medieval towns."}
{"id": "f0a95c1a-4fb6-4228-8b08-5cc8a8863555", "value": "An area of land and associated buildings where grapevines are cultivated."}
{"id": "c2ad5b0c-4f31-459f-a15c-351723b7286b", "value": "Large archaeological site presented to the public."}

{"id": "bb68231d-7058-4803-a4e2-c5faa3a6a8f7", "value": "Sea or river channels no longer charted or recorded as in active navigational use for present shipping traffic and with evidence that the channel is also now a buried feature (if extant at all)."}

{"id": "3ce16c3e-2d9d-4ad5-b89f-6050f0446306", "value": "A tower or structure, with a powerful light or lights at the top, usually erected at an important or dangerous point on or near the sea-coast for the warning and guidance of mariners, but may also be sited inland."}
{"id": "c7a6deb7-bb64-42ed-b3fc-51c9ce201938", "value": "Agricultural village with farmsteads and cottages wholly or mainly arranged around the edges of a green."}
{"id": "83530be6-5987-4ae0-8339-e00006edfbdc", "value": "Buildings and grounds where a group of devotees to a religion live and worship. Subdivide by form of religion, sect, etc."}

{"id": "b2ef109c-d488-43f5-b665-91f3d7803396", "value": "Relates to the area of the hazard which may include a single wreck or a cluster of several. Wrecks have greatest relevance from their roles as hazards to navigational activity, or as indicators of areas and routes of past navigational or trading activity."}
{"id": "633372b1-5e60-4919-b6aa-5846a3e04ff0", "value": "Indoor pool for sports such as swimming and diving. Includes any directly associated grounds."}
{"id": "a2c94491-31ff-4f25-9a58-6c6079245460", "value": "An enclosed piece of ground devoted to recreational purposes."}
{"id": "dc794375-99a1-41fa-a216-9cea988e11af", "value": "An area such as a commercial garden where plants and trees are grown and nurtured for the purpose of transportation or sale."}
{"id": "7bf20441-4057-4e64-8ca9-ab703ea01924", "value": "An enclosed piece of ground devoted to the cultivation of flowers, fruit or vegetables for domestic use."}
{"id": "681f6498-c3f0-46be-94af-07bdb2e22460", "value": "Building complex with yards etc, where horses are bred, raised and securely kept."}
{"id": "2bc0860d-662b-4cf8-a914-4786e581b587", "value": "Areas of the water column and/or sea surface characterised by heavy swell, strong currents and tidal races which pose a risk for navigation."}

{"id": "8f97a021-e6cb-45bd-b89d-3c02cda8be7f", "value": "An area used for recreational fishing and angling."}
{"id": "3b585a34-be8f-4985-80c4-20232e3a0faa", "value": "An area, building, site or structure associated with the hunting of animals."}
{"id": "a109aaaa-82f2-4308-86d6-cdbce4486fa6", "value": "Area used for recreational sailing, yachting, and other small craft pursuits."}
{"id": "578f7212-7474-441d-a926-ef331936617d", "value": "Provision for occasional accommodation for those who have travelled from home for enjoyment, amusement or pleasure."}
{"id": "51a43dec-0a41-4433-860d-90eac8cfc7b0", "value": "An area of closely mown lawn measured out and appropriately marked for use in the game of flat or crown green bowling."}
{"id": "e13e504c-05a9-4300-97cf-8fa5e85af0fa", "value": "A prison for the containment of servicemen captured in war."}
{"id": "22a33d28-4f7c-4d2f-a4cf-aa4f49547c39", "value": "An outdoor area, commonly on the coast, used by people predominantly for bathing and/or swimming."}
{"id": "03956a89-24bb-4d8d-b075-cb5c6c48c713", "value": "A place where china-clay (kaolin) is extracted and purified."}

{"id": "9a5791bf-15ac-4929-8749-ba59ec04eacf", "value": "Block of land within an open field system containing a number of individual strips and usually managed as a single cropping or farming unit. In places such blocks were associated with fixed lengths, hence also name for a customary length of 220 yards."}
{"id": "0523c9a9-8623-4160-b580-42ff2adfc181", "value": "A place where nickel ore is extracted. Also use with other metal ores extracted and MINE where relevant."}

{"id": "add400a2-7bb4-4da4-987b-cf6419b57848", "value": "A landscaped area of ground, encompassing different types of terrain and features, such as ponds, sand-filled bunkers etc, on which the game of golf is played."}

{"id": "cb427628-c6c6-4321-a40c-0ae97ae49d0a", "value": "Educational establishments awarding degrees and undertaking research. Includes buildings and directly associated and usually defined grounds."}
{"id": "4b7ac384-bf79-4279-b0a3-9e46b5d8209b", "value": "A site, building or factory used for the production of salt."}
{"id": "323eb9bd-5ad0-44db-b3ec-c551d7f30066", "value": "Sites, buildings or structures associated with the entire process of salt production by various means."}
{"id": "b1ae9206-ed83-4223-9277-910c6f56c430", "value": "Plantations dominated by broadleaved trees, including areas of planting, ground ripping, immature or mature stands, felled areas."}
{"id": "39a1681a-21ab-40e5-bc9c-b867f8e2a9bf", "value": "A farm concerned with the cultivation of flowering and ornamental plants for gardens and for floristry."}
{"id": "f12c8306-c132-4851-b48d-ec467f4a2877", "value": "A small settlement containing two or more farmsteads, but few amenities. Typical rural settlement form away from central province."}
{"id": "462ecbd5-335b-4fc9-8483-e74e52fb6638", "value": "An area of ground used for the testing of, and practicing with armoured tanks."}

{"id": "214df97f-732f-4717-8c64-59db03651634", "value": "A form of sea defence, may be of hard and strong material (eg concrete) or an earthen bank constructed on the landward part of a coast to reduce the effects of strong waves."}
{"id": "5d8d3c45-34d1-4a52-aa29-345bb4f14ace", "value": "An area deemed hazardous due to a predominance of recorded obstructions and fouls not known to be associated with a wreck."}
{"id": "bf4ea74d-a4a8-40af-ad10-966efc7642bf", "value": "An area of the sea, a lake, or a river where the water is not very deep."}

{"id": "42222bd0-5978-4a95-989f-da747d77705d", "value": "Areas that contain serious risks to vessels which could lead to their damage or complete loss. Such risks may be directly related to sea floor features and aspects, such as wrecks and other seafloor debris and obstructions."}

{"id": "05596872-268a-427e-b973-28eef418a1a9", "value": "Areas dominated by rocks rising from the general level of the seabed but not breaking the surface of the water at any state of the tide, posing a risk for navigation."}
{"id": "455edf96-97af-4f5a-aac2-59cb323cc277", "value": "An area where motor vehicles are stored, often associated with commerce."}
{"id": "a76e0bc1-ca9f-40ab-a5ec-69ec868bc719", "value": "A fortified building or site with purpose-built emplacements for artillery pieces."}

Single or arrangements of buoys, beacons and lights are often used to demarcate safely navigable entrances to estuaries and rivers, submerged hazards and foul areas."}

{"id": "fbba0fcd-9a11-457a-98f5-bd8a15970f2b", "value": "A commercial complex, usually sited along motorways or trunk roads, providing facilities such as car parking, restaurants, shop and fuel stations."}
{"id": "934cfde6-5565-4f90-acde-95e1da64757c", "value": "Hamlet for accommodation of industrial workers, usually close to either extractive industry or milling."}
{"id": "bdda7b55-3033-4006-8300-8f1d2fad88ce", "value": "A settlement area that combines a harbour and terminal facilities at the interface between land and water transportation systems."}

{"id": "3b1b22b6-3ff2-4c86-989f-083e7fa8fd52", "value": "Largely inter-tidal areas, predominantly of sand, used mostly for leisure and relaxation by coastal visitors. May be managed actively, eg by periodic scraping or beach replenishment, or passively, eg by groynes, to retain the sand cover."}
{"id": "3c9415cc-fcee-49b0-975e-15884c629464", "value": "A town notable for hosting on a regular basis a market, usually for agricultural products, including livestock."}
{"id": "293fa105-15a4-403a-b7c9-26945a889627", "value": "A series of structures extending into the sea for the purpose of preventing further lateral movement of washed up sand and shingle."}
{"id": "5dfe6229-354e-4fb8-85f1-f9cded2878f0", "value": "An area, often consisting of widened streets or a town square used for regular or occasional markets."}
{"id": "6ba311a3-2966-4806-a59d-116712973f78", "value": "An area of foreshore where the predominant cover is exposed bedrock."}
